>Copying text to multiple destinations is missing (IMHO) in Xedit.
>Does anyone know a way to do this without redefining the source block
>(or line) each time?

The way I do it is:

 1) Make the first line of the block the current line.

 2) PUT or PUTD  with a target or number of lines

 3) Make the line you want the block to follow the current line.

 4) GET

 5) Repeat 3 & 4 as many times as desired.
